CODE 1 :-
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
# -------------------- LOAD DATASET --------------------
df = sns.load_dataset("iris")
print("========== DATA PREVIEW ==========")
print(df.head())
print("\n========== FEATURES & DATA TYPES ==========")
print(df.dtypes)
# -------------------- HISTOGRAMS --------------------
print("\n========== HISTOGRAMS ==========")
df.hist(figsize=(10,8))
plt.suptitle("Histograms of Iris Features")
plt.show()
# -------------------- BOXPLOTS --------------------
print("\n========== BOXPLOTS ==========")
features = df.columns[:-1] # exclude species
for col in features:
plt.figure()
sns.boxplot(x="species", y=col, data=df)
plt.title(f"Boxplot of {col}")
plt.show()
# -------------------- BASIC OBSERVATIONS PRINT --------------------
print("\n========== OBSERVATIONS ==========")
print("1. Sepal features show overlap between species.")
print("2. Petal features clearly separate species.")
print("3. Some outliers are present in sepal_width.")
print("4. Petal length and width are most important features.")

###Explaination 

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
Explanation
import pandas as pd

Imports the Pandas library.

Used for handling datasets in table form (DataFrame).

pd is a short name for pandas.

import seaborn as sns

Imports Seaborn library.

Used for data visualization (graphs, plots).

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

Imports Matplotlib plotting functions.

plt is used to display graphs.

LOAD DATASET
df = sns.load_dataset("iris")
Explanation
Loads the Iris flower dataset from Seaborn.

Dataset contains flower measurements.
Example Dataset Values
sepal_length	sepal_width	petal_length	petal_width	species
5.1	3.5	1.4	0.2	setosa
4.9	3.0	1.4	0.2	setosa
6.3	3.3	6.0	2.5	virginica
Meaning of Columns
sepal_length → length of sepal
sepal_width → width of sepal
petal_length → length of petal
petal_width → width of petal
species → flower type

print("========== DATA PREVIEW ==========")
Explanation
Prints heading on screen.

Output
========== DATA PREVIEW ==========
print(df.head())
Explanation
head() displays first 5 rows of dataset.
Example Output
sepal_length	sepal_width	petal_length	petal_width	species
5.1	3.5	1.4	0.2	setosa
4.9	3.0	1.4	0.2	setosa
Purpose:
To quickly check dataset values.

DATA TYPES
print("\n========== FEATURES & DATA TYPES ==========")
