###########Important Oral Questions

What is histogram?
A graph showing frequency distribution of data.

What is boxplot?
A graph showing spread, median, quartiles, and outliers.

Why use df.hist()?
To create histograms for numeric features.

Why exclude species column?
Because it is categorical/text data.

Which features best separate species?
Petal length and petal width.

What are outliers?
Unusual values far from other data points.

What does df.head() do?
Displays first 5 rows.

What does df.dtypes do?
Shows datatype of each column.


